Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_ideal_network(25.10)                              set_ideal_network(25.10)

Name
       set_ideal_network  -  Identifies  driver pins or ports as sources of an
       ideal network

Syntax
       set_ideal_network

       <object_list>

       [-no_propagate]

       Identifies driver pins or ports as sources of an ideal network. By  de-
       fault, all pins and nets in the transitive fanout of the specified port
       or driver pin are marked as ideal. Ideal network marking normally prop-
       agates through combinational cells and stops at sequential cells.

       Note:  This  command is not view/mode-based - it applies to all the ac-
       tive views.

       The set_ideal_network command sets 0 slew for bi-directional pins. This
       ensures that unnecessary DRV violations do not occur.

Parameters
       -no_propagate
              Prevents propagation through transitive fanout.

       <object_list>
              Specifies a list of objects - instance pins, ports, or nets.

Examples
              * The following command marks  the  fanout  of  the  input  port
                scan_se as an ideal network:

                > set_ideal_network scan_se

                This  can  be  observed  in  the output of below mentioned re-
                port_timing command where the whole  fanout  of  'scan_se'  is
                considered as ideal :

                > report_timing -from scan_se

                Path     1:     MET     Setup     Check     with    Pin    RE-
                SULTS_CONV_INST/r697_reg[12]/CK

